article.headline: Wesby has 20 points and nine rebounds for Temple
article.linkText: Owls, Wesby handle local rival Drexel
article.story:
PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Alex Wesby had 20 points and nine rebounds
as Temple defeated local rival Drexel, 68-59, in the opening round
of the Owens Corning National Invitation Tournament on Tuesday night.

	   Despite the fact that the teams are located six miles apart,
they had not met since the NCAA Tournament in 1994.

	   Brian Polk and Maurice Collins each had 11 points and David
Hawkins scored 10 points for the Owls (16-15), who have won nine of
11 and will play Boston College in the next round. 

Temple, which is
in the postseason for the 20th consecutive season, advanced to the
championship game of the Atlantic 10 Conference tournament before
losing to Dayton, 79-72.

	   Kenell Sanchez had 16 points, Tim Whitworth scored 13 and Eric
Schmeider added 12 for the Dragons (19-12), who were in the
postseason for the first time since 1997. Robert Battle had 13
rebounds and five blocks for Drexel, which lost to North
Carolina-Wilmington, 70-62, in the championship game of the
Colonial Athletic Association tournament.

	   Temple, which trailed 30-29 at halftime, scored the first 11
points of the second half and 23 of the first 30 points. A driving
layup by Antywane Robinson made it 52-37 with 8:50 left. The
Dragons were unable to get closer than nine.

	   A 3-pointer by Schmeider made it 30-23 with 2:49 left in the
first half, Drexel's biggest lead, but the Owls scored the last six
points of the half to pull within one at the break.
